  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Small-Scale Dairy Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmer households, Women, Youth</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Heifer Ghana is expanding its animal portfolio over the next five years to include dairy goats and dairy cattle. This project, funded in part by Heifer Netherlands, will distribute 140 dairy cattle and 144 dairy goats to 200 families in six communities&#x2014;Dodowa, Kasoa, Aburi, Nsawam, Mamfe and Abokobi&#x2014;within a 20-mile radius. Each family will receive either one dairy heifer or two dairy goats. In addition to learning about a new zero-grazing farming system, project farmers will also learn about project management, gender equity and HIV/AIDS prevention. Passing on the gift will benefit an additional 200 families over five years.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Select project families using agreed criteria; Train dairy farm families on dairy cattle cow management; Organize exposure visits to neighbouring countries for key staff and 6 farmer motivators; Train farmers on co-operatives management and micro-enterprise development; Sensitize farm families on HIV and gender issues; Distribute 140 dairy cattle in 6 communities; Train 12 community Livestock Workers; Train project participants in milk handling and milk preservation technologies.</narrative>
  </description>
